  "prompt": "What are some good libraries in Mumbai?",
  "response": "Mumbai has a rich literary scene and offers several libraries that cater to different interests. Here are some notable libraries in the city:\n\n1. **The Asiatic Society of Mumbai**: One of the oldest libraries in the city, it houses rare books, manuscripts, and a vast collection of historical documents.\n\n2. **The British Council Library**: This library focuses on English-language materials and offers a wide range of books, magazines, and resources for learning and research.\n\n3. **The National Gallery of Modern Art (NGMA) Library**: Located at Kala Ghoda, this library has a collection focused on modern art, along with research materials and publications.\n\n4. **Mumbai University Library**: The university library holds a vast collection of academic books, journals, and research papers for students and researchers.\n\n5. **The Kala Ghoda Association Library**: This community library offers books across various genres and is a great place for local literature enthusiasts.\n\n6. **G. N. Khalsa College Library**: Located in Byculla, this library is known for its academic resources and significant collection of books.\n\n7. **Nehru Science Centre Library**: Catering to those interested in science and technology, this library provides access to a range of scientific literature.\n\n8. **P. L. Deshpande Maharashtra Kala Academy Library**: This library focuses on literature related to Marathi arts and culture.\n\n9. **The Mumbai Public Library**: With branches across the city, this public library aims to provide access to a variety of books for all age groups.\n\n10. **K. R. Cama Oriental Institute Library**: Known for its collection of books on oriental studies, history, and culture.\n\nThese libraries often host events, workshops, and discussions that contribute to Mumbai\u2019s vibrant intellectual community. Make sure to check their websites or contact them for details about access and membership.",
